arian -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAll of the papers included in this volume offer some novel and/or updated perspective on issues of central importance in pragmatics, suggesting original ways in which research in the particular areas they adhere to could advance. Apart from the obvious aim of motivating further discussion on the topics it touches on, a central objective of this volume is to underline that research in pragmatics can and does substantially inform research in numerous other fields of enquiry, namely philosophy, cognitive science, linguistics and conversation analysis, revealing in this way the truly interdisciplinary nature of pragmatics theorizing. In this respect, and given that most of the contributions in this volume are from leading scholars in their respective fields, it is clearly expected that the ideas put forth in this volume will have a profound and long-lasting impact for future research in the area.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aIntercultural communicationvCongresses. 0aLanguage and culturevCongresses. 0aPragmaticsvCongresses. 4aKognitive Linguistik. 4aPragmatik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aConversational Analysis.  aLinguistics.  aPhilosophy.  aPragmatics.1 aAssimakopoulos, Stavros, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAssimakopoulos, Stavros, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBabarczy, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChiou, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFretheim, Thorstein, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorta, Kepa, econtributor.4